rComments: you have to read the textbook. The quizzes were challenging but doable. The paper however was not good. She had a strict page limit and did not have a good rubric (you have to go beyond the rubric to even get an A-). She taught well and her exam was fair but the paper was unfair and the amount of reading she assigns is ridiculous

Amélie's part of our course was fairly straightforward and the quiz questions tended to be quite reflective of what we were taught in lecture. However, in her term paper, she told me after submission that the rubric is not indicative of what you should actually include, and I lost marks for random things not listed on there or covered in lecture.
